# Narratives

> The stories you tell yourself (and others) about the world - the frames your work operates within.

_Not yet captured. Fill via `/interview` (Phase 1) or by talking to your DA._

## Notes

Narratives are the "elevator pitch" versions of your missions and beliefs combined. They're what you'd say in a conference intro line, on your About page, or in a first-meeting pitch.

A good narrative is *memorable* and *lossless* - it compresses the big picture without losing what's distinctive.

---
*The DA references narratives when drafting content, public communication, or framing pitches. Consistency across channels comes from a stable narrative surface.*
